content.description: Follow an obvious left-trending crack in an overhanging corner until it disappears. Use a bad crimp and two-finger pocket to lunge right to a pretty good pocket on the face.  A big move will lead to some techy climbing to reach the chains.
content.location: Starts at the base of the obvious left-trending crack in an overhanging corner.  About 30 feet to the left of Hot Milk about halfway down the hill.

content.description: Start by reaching for a layback flake that climbs past the first few bolts to a large pocket. Move up onto thin holds and good pockets over great stone to the anchor.
content.location: About 80 feet to the right of 'Wyoming Wave'(the obvious bolted wave), on the right side of the clean white wall.

content.description:
Located between 'Little Man' and 'Hot Milk' at the 'Sphinx Wall'.

A nice little route with several bouldery cruxes on good stone.

Hard moves off the ground continue to a great rest at about mid height, then a few more hard moves lead to a monster jug at the anchor.

Start with hard moves off the ground for the first few clips. Continue on bigger holds over easier terrain to the anchor.

Good rock, nice pockets, and fun moves make this a fun climb.
content.location:
The far left side of the Sphinx Wall.

"10d" is currently written in chalk at the base of the route.

content.description: For a 50 foot route this packs a punch.  Between the tenuous start , dyno that is actually a deadpoint, and figuring out how to skip all of the micro holds that really aren't needed you are in for a ride.  Piecing it all together is key if you are going to send.
content.location: This is just up the hill from the main Sphinx wall on a short black wall.
